1
00:00:03,829 --> 00:00:08,079
Śrīla Gurudev, expressing
very high things, but as a basis,

2
00:00:08,079 --> 00:00:13,372
saying, “First, realise that
you are a worm in a bucket of stool.”

3
00:00:13,372 --> 00:00:16,746
[You Will Not Die!]

4
00:00:16,746 --> 00:00:22,328
“Oh, Mahārāj, how can you say
something so ugly,

5
00:00:22,328 --> 00:00:24,972
and with a big smile?”

6
00:00:24,972 --> 00:00:28,541
Because he’s telling the truth
from that position.

7
00:00:28,541 --> 00:00:32,143
And Guru Mahārāj, if you want to take
the similar example

8
00:00:32,143 --> 00:00:34,088
and rephrase it in a nicer way,
he said,

9
00:00:34,088 --> 00:00:42,768
“Would you rather be the king
of a mountain of stuff here—stool?

10
00:00:42,768 --> 00:00:48,659
Or a worm in a bucket of nectar there?”

11
00:00:48,659 --> 00:00:53,722
Śṛṇvantu viśve amṛtasya putrā 
[Su: 2.5]—

12
00:00:53,998 --> 00:00:56,911
you are children of the nectar world,

13
00:00:56,911 --> 00:01:01,863
of the nectar soil—not the mṛtyu world,

14
00:01:01,863 --> 00:01:05,098
the world of mortality,
it’s not your home—

15
00:01:05,098 --> 00:01:07,511
but the immortal world.

16
00:01:07,511 --> 00:01:12,794
“Tvaḿ tu rājan mariṣyeti
paśu-buddhim imāḿ jahi”:

17
00:01:12,794 --> 00:01:16,851
after all the rāsa-līlā and all these
high, wonderful things

18
00:01:16,851 --> 00:01:19,191
—rāsa-līlā, Uddhava-gītā—

19
00:01:19,191 --> 00:01:21,676
what does Sūkadev at last
tell Parīkṣit Mahārāj?

20
00:01:21,676 --> 00:01:26,789
“Thinking that you will die,
that’s animal intelligence,

21
00:01:26,789 --> 00:01:30,199
don’t think like that. You won’t die.”
[SB: 12.5.2]

22
00:01:30,199 --> 00:01:32,854
Why?
Śṛṇvantu viśve amṛtasya putrā:

23
00:01:32,854 --> 00:01:36,436
You’re a child of the nectar world,
of the nectar soil.

24
00:01:36,436 --> 00:01:47,483
Amṛtam, mṛtyu. ‘Amṛtam’ means
‘no mṛtyu; no death; immortality.’

